the decide rules, the status in place is the one used, so even if your Matc=
hesListRegexDecideRule rejects the URI, a later rule may change that status=
 to ACCEPT. For example, your regex might rule out the URI, but if after th=
at rule you have a TransclusionDecideRule, that &quot;accepts any URI whose path=
-from-seed ends in at least one non-navlink hop&quot; (https://webarchive.jira.c=
om/wiki/display/Heritrix/Configuring+Crawl+Scope+Using+DecideRules) and is =
generally used to accept embedded content such as images and videos no matt=
er the URI pattern, the URI would be ruled back in to acceptance. You could=
 try moving your MatchesListRegexDecideRule lower in the chain of rules and=
 see if that helps.
